JOHN F. BETZ & SON, Limited, Claimant of 27 Tanks of Beer, etc., Appellant, v. UNITED STATES, Appellee. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Third Circuit. February 11, 1926.) No. 3409. William A. Gray and Walter Willard, both of Philadelphia, Pa., for appellant. Francis B. Biddle, Asst. U. S. Atty., and George W. Coles, U. S. Atty., both of Philadelphia, Pa.

Before BUFFINGTON, WOOLLEY, and DAVIS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

There is not enough in

this case to distinguish it from Daeufer-Lieberman Brewing Co. v. United States (C. C. A.) 8 F.(2d) 1. As it is ruled by the law of the latter case, the decree of the District Court is reversed.
